.TH "KENNEL" "1" "" "Project Kennel" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
kennel \- run and manage confined workloads (kennels)
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBkennel\fR \fIcommand\fR [\fIargs\fR...]
.SH DESCRIPTION
kennel is the command\-line front\-end to Project Kennel, a security sandbox that runs a workload (an AI coding agent, a build, a service) under a signed policy. Each invocation of \fBkennel run\fR is one kennel: its own context, cgroup, constructed filesystem view, masked identity, per\-kennel network namespace, and egress proxy, all torn down when the workload exits.
.PP
The CLI talks to the per\-user \fBkenneld\fR(8) daemon over a control socket; kenneld constructs and supervises the kennel. Policy authoring (compile, sign, validate, lint) is done locally by the CLI and needs no daemon.
.PP
Run \fBkennel \fIcommand\fB \-\-help\fR for a command's usage. The policy sub\-verbs have their own page, \fBkennel\-policy\fR(1).
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
\fBkennel run <policy> [<name>] [\-\-key K] [\-\-force] [\-\-template\-dir D]... [\-\-trust\-dir D]... [\-\- <cmd...>]\fR
run a workload confined by a policy, in the foreground
.RS
.TP
\fB\-\-key K\fR
Sign the in\-memory compiled policy with key K for the local\-dev run loop (auto\-compile).
.RE
.RS
.TP
\fB\-\-force\fR
Override a [workload] pinned argv with a CLI \-\- command.
.RE
.RS
.TP
\fB\-\- <cmd...>\fR
The command to run inside the kennel (overrides [workload].argv unless pinned).
.RE
.RS
.TP
\fB\-\-template\-dir D\fR
Add a directory to the template/fragment search path (repeatable). Overrides the config.toml default cascade.
.RE
.RS
.TP
\fB\-\-trust\-dir D\fR
Add a directory to the signing\-key trust store used while authoring (repeatable).
.RE
.TP
\fBkennel attach <name>\fR
reattach a terminal to a running kennel (Ctrl\-\ d to detach)
.TP
\fBkennel review <policy> [\-\-yes]\fR
review + re\-pin a workspace's trust manifest after legitimate edits
.TP
\fBkennel stop <name>\fR
stop a running kennel
.RS
.TP
\fB(sub\-verbs)\fR
See kennel\-policy(1) for list, show, edit, generate, compile, validate, sign, lint.
.RE
.TP
\fBkennel list\fR
list running kennels
.RS
.TP
\fB\-\-dir DIR\fR
Write the key pair to DIR instead of the default key store.
.RE
.RS
.TP
\fB\-\-force\fR
Overwrite an existing key of the same id.
.RE
.TP
\fBkennel policy <list|show|edit|generate|compile|validate|sign|lint|risks|upgrade> [...]\fR
author, inspect, sign, and check policies
.RS
.TP
\fBadd\fR
Append a provably\-valid allocation line for a uid (collision\-free tag/gid).
.RE
.RS
.TP
\fBcheck\fR
Validate the allocation file and report malformed lines.
.RE
.RS
.TP
\fB\-\-uid N\fR
The target uid (defaults to the caller).
.RE
.RS
.TP
\fB\-\-namespace NS\fR
The allocation namespace.
.RE
.RS
.TP
\fB\-\-tag N\fR
A specific 12\-bit tag (otherwise allocated).
.RE
.RS
.TP
\fB\-\-file PATH\fR
Operate on PATH instead of /etc/kennel/subkennel.
.RE
.TP
\fBkennel keygen <key\-id> [\-\-dir DIR] [\-\-force]\fR
generate a policy\-signing key
.RS
.TP
\fB\-\-resource CLASS\fR
Filter to one class (network, filesystem, exec, ...).
.RE
.RS
.TP
\fB\-\-since DUR\fR
Only events newer than DUR (e.g. 1h, 30m).
.RE
.RS
.TP
\fB\-\-novel\-only\fR
Suppress events seen in a prior run (new events only).
.RE
.RS
.TP
\fB\-\-follow\fR
Stream new events as they arrive.
.RE
.RS
.TP
\fB\-\-print\-journalctl\-command\fR
Print the equivalent journalctl invocation and exit.
.RE
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
\fB0\fR
Success. For kennel run, the workload's own exit code is passed through (clamped to a byte).
.TP
\fB1\fR
Generic failure: the CLI could not reach kenneld, a file could not be read, or kenneld returned an error.
.TP
\fB3\fR
Policy validation or resolution failure: schema, invariants, template inheritance, or include conflict.
.TP
\fB6\fR
Signature or lockfile\-pin failure during resolution.
.TP
\fB7\fR
kennel policy lint found at least one coherence finding across the template corpus.
.SH FILES
.TP
\fI/usr/libexec/kennel/\fR
The helper binaries kenneld resolves (see kennel\-helpers via the .8 pages).
.TP
\fI~/.config/kennel/config.toml\fR
User CLI conveniences (search paths). See config.toml(5).
.TP
\fI/etc/kennel/subkennel\fR
Per\-user kennel allocations. See subkennel(5).
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
\fBkennel run ai\-coding\-strict \-\- claude\fR
Run Claude Code confined by the ai\-coding\-strict template.
.TP
\fBkennel run ./policy.toml myjob\fR
Auto\-compile and run a local source policy as kennel 'myjob'.
.TP
\fBkennel list\fR
Show running kennels.
.TP
\fBkennel audit myjob \-\-follow\fR
Stream myjob's audit log.
.SH SEE ALSO
\fBkennel\-policy\fR(1), \fBkenneld\fR(8), \fBpolicy.toml\fR(5), \fBconfig.toml\fR(5), \fBsystem.toml\fR(5), \fBsubkennel\fR(5)
